description: Fans of Big Nate will love this hilarious graphic novel about the end of the world - and the dogs and cats left behind! Brownie, Apollo, and their ragtag group of strays have raided the grocery store and defeated some very mean mutts - but now they've run out of food. So when the crew discovers a nearby Twonkies factory, and all the Twonkies they could ever eat, they think they've got it made. The only catch is the cat guarding the factory - and this "cat" is much bigger, and far more sophisticated, than any feline they've ever met. Can the dogs and their friends defeat their foe and claim the Twonkies for themselves?
name: GN

description: Edward Reed is a unique artist who delights in the old-school masters of pin-up like Vargas, Elvgren and Petty, yet he has a fascination for photo-realism that borders on the surreal. Also an in-demand instructor, Edward has assembled a fascinating step-by-step to show how he creates such intricate and amazing masterworks.
name: HC

volume.name: The Art of Edward Reed: Portraits & Pin-Ups

description:
Foundations

Chapter 01 of Avaiyo, Vol. 03

Heading back to Brosha, Sekken and Iyo meet up with their guild, Emerald Moon. Reunions are cut short as a new crisis emerges that has the means to threaten the entire world. With little time to spare, they depart for Preminx...in hopes of heading off the Dark Legion. With Emerald Moon standing between two armies, it is their hope the Region of Preminx will not be soaked in blood.
name: Foundations

description: Since Joss Whedon has been understandingly busy lately, someone needs to satisfy your hunger for a dark, supernatural, but comedic story. Kevin West and Jose Marzan do a fantastic job making Bayou Bound, the epic tale that you will read over and over. Writer Jeff Kaufman, known for his "kick you in your face endings," has drafted a story that can't help but to amuse and confuse. It's about a 22-year-old guy stuck in Wildwood, Louisiana, where he gets deputized to handle all of the town's supernatural cases. Think Buffy meets Eureka.
name: GN

description: Contains Subject 38 - 43.
name: Vol. 8

description: BOO! is back! Your host Mister Puzzles returns to bring you 15 brand new tales of humor and horror from a murderer's row of spooky storytellers!

Featuring "Modesty Blaise" in "Honeygun" by Peter O'Donnell and Romero. Color features include chapter 8 of the very first Mandrake Sunday story, "The Hidden Kingdom of Murderers." Other features include The Phantom by Wilson McCoy, Flash Gordon by Mac Raboy, Gasoline Alley by Dick Moores, Tarzan by Russ Manning, Alley Oop by V. T. Hamlin, Casey Ruggles by Warren Tufts, and Steve Canyon by Milton Caniff.

To rescue their loved ones from the insatiable Ruleians, Jack and Mo seek the aid of a pair of antisocial outcasts, and get way more than they bargained for. Meanwhile, the humans trapped in orbit by their hungry extraterrestrial kidnappers find an unlikely ally! The sci-fi, punk rock adventure from writer Sam Read (Find) and artist Caio Oliveira (Super Ego) continues; make sure you jump aboard!

name: Part Two

description: Give Me Liberty or Give Me Obamacare is a trenchant and hilarious collection of political cartoons, presenting a wonderfully intelligent and beautifully drawn snapshot of the absurdities of the Obama presidency. Michael Ramirez is a two-time winner of the Pulitzer Prize in 1994 and 2008 and a three-time Sigma Delta Chi, Society of Professional Journalism Award winner. Ramirez tackles everything from Obamacare to the economy, foreign policy to culture wars, the environment, and much more.
name: TPB

volume.name: Give Me Liberty Or Give Me Obamacare

description: Check out the comic that IO9 calls "A terribly fun read"! Mary Posa hates her job. She works long hours for little pay, no insurance, and, worst of all, no respect. Her coworkers are jerks and her boss doesn't appreciate her. He's also happens to be a supervillain. Cursed with a conscience, Mary would give anything to be something other than a Henchgirl!

From John Carpenter, the man who brought you the cult classic horror film Halloween and all of the scares beyond comes the ultimate graphic novel anthology of tales to warm your toes by on a dark and stormy October night! Carpenter brings together storytellers from the worlds of movies, novels and comics for a collection of tales featuring graveyards, sunken ships, creepy crawlers and ghosts to haunt your dreams at night!
name: Volume 1

volume.name: John Carpenter's Tales For A HalloweeNight

description: Frank Robbins' masterpiece, one of the all-time greatest action/adventure newspaper comic strips, Johnny Hazard, returns with Volume Four of the series! Continues the adventures of Johnny Hazard picking up the storyline where Volume Three left off. See more trend-setting artwork by comics legend Frank Robbins in one of the most important adventure strips ever to grace newspapers. Reproduced entirely from original King Features press proofs covering daily strips from 1949-1951.
name: Volume Four: 1949-1951

description:
Josephine is plagued by misfortunes, but she is often her own worst enemy; she manages her professional relations and work poorly, struggles to be understood, is prone to blunders, and her love life is a succession of faux pas...

Fortunately, Josephine is divine... And divinely funny!
name: Not That Bad 2/2

description:
The grand finale of The Tablet of Destinies! Lady Mechanika attempts a daring rescue of the Professor and Winifred, but there may be more at stake than she realized. What mysterious secret has the Professor uncovered to provoke such extreme measures from the German secret police? And what will Lady Mechanika do when forced to choose between the lives of her friends and the fate of all humankind?

description: Amal just called off his arranged marriage, came out of the closet, got disowned, and went on a bender. Now TJ, a complete stranger, tells him they've made a drunken pact to drive all the way from Berkeley to Providence. Amal needs to get there for his sister's graduation. TJ has his own reasons. The Less Than Epic Adventures of TJ and Amal omnibus collects the full 2009-2014 run of E.K. Weaver's critically acclaimed road trip romance, with brand new full-color inserts!
name: GN

volume.name: The Less Than Epic Adventures of TJ and Amal

description: Mercy Sparx, heaven's unorthodox enforcer, thought her life was about to get easier after finally escaping from Club Nephilim (vol. 2), but life just got more complicated. Her past actions have caused problems for her ally / Shaman / Voodoo master Wallace Bordeaux, her (literally) monster of an ex-boyfriend is stuck on Earth and couch surfing up in her apartment, and her mother has plans to make life (literally, again) HELL on Earth.
name: Volume 3

volume.name: Mercy Sparx: Family Roots [Of All Evil]

description: While searching a bone-littered clearing, Maia and crew are attacked by a Fear Liath, a monstrous beast that seems unstoppable. Maia's bodyguard-the kishion-leaps into battle, risking his life to save her. But Maia has more to worry about than just the Fear Liath. As the fight ensues, the soldiers accompanying Maia grow suspicious and fearful of her magical abilities, branding her an abomination worthy of death.

There exists a world of horrors beneath the one we know, where the creatures of our nightmares stalk amongst humanity. The Chain polices this world, a covert agency of killer monsters keeping the human herd from growing too thin. Introduction by Kieron Gillen.
name: Volume 1

description:
Overstreet's Comic Book Marketplace Yearbook 2015-2016 features a special look Dean Mullaney's Eclipse Comics, their impact on creator ownership, manga, and more. Also in the spotlight are Valiant Entertainment's big Hollywood plans; the 75th anniversaries of Wonder Woman, Green Lantern, and Hawkman; the 25th anniversary of Cable; the incredible first year of Static; Marvel-ous self-promotion in F.O.O.M. and Marvel Age; interviews with Sal Buscema, Paul Ryan, Steve Epting, and the late Jerry Robinson; plus Corto Maltese, Dinosaurs for Hire, The Black Hood, Fireside books, market reports, and much more - all from the publishers of The Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide!

Guy Delisle, author of Jerusalem: Chronicles from the Holy City and A User's Guide to Neglectful Parenting, shares nineteen all-new comic strips that pay tribute to all the ways parents can drive their kids crazy, and vice versa. Slipping grammar lessons into bedtime stories, being challenged by difficult toys, and pretending to forget you even have a son: it's all in a day's work for Delisle. In The Owner's Manual, Delisle doesn't hesitate to make a slightly bumbling, fictionalized version of himself the butt of the joke, though his children often contribute zingy repartee and laugh-out-loud insight in the stories on display here. The Owner's Manual is the perfect antidote to frustrating car rides filled with "Are we there yet?" and epic battles over homework.
name: GN

volume.name: The Owner's Manual To Terrible Parenting

description: It’s romance, unbridled lust, and the scandalous relationship of a lesbian and her best friend… all while being a man in your forties? Thanks to a chemical leak, all the teenage girls in Tokyo have magically turned into middle aged salarymen! Who knew sexiness came with bald spots, parted hair, and neatly-trimmmed mustaches? Chinatsu and Tomoe were the best friends two teenage girls could have, but will they be something more as over-the-hill office workers? They’ll trade in their short skirts for business casual in OYAJINA! CHINATSU AND TOMOE.
name: Vol. 1

description: Dr. Huntington has captured Piggy and his team. Now, Huntington's ultimate plan will finally be revealed, and only our caped canine can stop him, but not without a little help. Don't miss the final issue of the mini-series!

Ever had a crappy job? Well, Poopert sure does! He's a poop working at Poop Office. Thrill at his adventures interacting with his officemates Fecelia, Alpoop, Buttany, his boss Mr. Poopson, and many more!

The sixth issue features more tales from the only office staffed entirely by poop! Discover the comic stylings of Poop Office's own Dook Poopson. Find out what Poopert plans to do with his new pooperclip holder! Revisit the challenges of the poopluck lunch in the 100th episode of Poop Office. Also what the poop's might be up to if Poop Office ever ends with a series of smelly spin-off ideas!

Includes Poop Office episodes 79-100, Shorts 55-60, and several spin-offs!

THIS MONTH'S COVER ART: New projects from Dynamite Entertainment and DC Comics!

THIS MONTH'S THEME: From the Archives-Classic Comics Collections!

Since 1988, PREVIEWS has been your ultimate source for all of the comics and merchandise to be available from your local comic book shop... revealed up to two months in advance! Hundreds of comics and graphic novels from the best comic publishers; the coolest pop-culture merchandise on Earth; plus PREVIEWS exclusive items available nowhere else! Now more than ever, PREVIEWS is here to show the tales, toys and treasures in your future! This November issue features items scheduled to ship in January 2016 and beyond.

Teenager Sydney Marie Woodman is a direct descendant of Red Riding Hood, pledged from birth to an 800-year-old war between the Order of the Red Hood and the savage Bloodwolves of the Underworld. Sydney must protect not only the Order but keep all mankind from the brink of extinction. And still find time to prep for the SAT's.

Alex hosts a tea party and makes new friends. Drew soars through the sky, searching for adventure. Two kids play in a park, imagining they're somewhere else. The worlds of imagination and reality collide in this wordless comic. In this clever wordless comic, Lee Nordling's simple storytelling engages young readers and provides a gateway into understanding multiple perspectives and points of view.
name: GN

description: Sketching Times gathers sketches from a global selection of artists in a broad range of techniques and styles, providing readers a window into the artistic process from the earliest of creative stages. Hand-picked by the featured artists, the title includes a wide variety of sketches that run from rough starts of what will become fantastic illustrations to pieces so intricate they seem to be finished projects already. Readers will find sketches ranging from bare-bones pencil sketches and free-flowing watercolor tests to the beginnings of stark computer graphics and cheeky character doodles.

volume.name: Sketching Times: Inspiration From 25 Artists' Sketch Collections

description: Having seemingly gained the upper hand over Spring-Heeled Jack, Doyle and Bell decide to confront him in his lair, deep under the streets of London. However our duo will find that they may have just made another mistake. One that might be their last. Does our duo have what it takes to stop The Terror of London once and for all? Find out in this thrilling conclusion to the series.

Finally Lee's dream comes true, as she moves from her native Hong Kong to her dream location: the UK. And with her dream handsome guy: Matt. Exciting! But of course, then comes the reality of being in a new country, of actually living together, and that might not be so easy, especially as Matt's best friend, Richard, seems more than a little jealous. And once again, wise Uncle Jun turns up to offer his advice. With art by Nami Tamura, a Japanese artist published by Kodansha.
name: Volume 2

description: This compilation of comic books from the early years of Superman reveals his involvement in World War II. Superman was not like any previous comic book character. He was the first costumed man with two identities, who possessed extraordinary strength and powers. He would protect the public when ordinary measures would not do. He was not the first super hero, but the Man of Steel would become the prototype for all super heroes thereafter.
name: HC

description: Tainted is a beautifully-illustrated graphic novel by the brilliant Chris Cross, whose style is amazing and unforgettable. Written by the notorious indie writer Jeff Kaufman, it takes an unusual twist on the whole vampires vs. the world genre and gives it a more human flavor. It follows a vampire named Smoke, who has been driven insane by a bad meal and is now being hunted by friends and foes. There is absolutely no sunshine or sparkling vampires in this book, just a great story.
name: GN

description: TALES OF MR. RHEE: “Karmageddon” is a 100 page survivalist horror graphic novel about five orphaned siblings who, when faced with nowhere else to go, choose to align with a mysterious magician named Mr. Rhee as Cthulhu, hordes of demons, and the Rapture sweep across the Earth.
name: Volume 2

description: The first book by YouTube star Joe Sugg is about Evie, a socially-isolated teenage girl who is given the opportunity to save the virtual world, which her father created for her, from descending into chaos. All the while, she must fend off high school bullies and help her ailing father. It's sweet adventure story for the millennial generation.
name: Volume 1

description: Showside is just your average southern town, except that portals to the Nexus realm keep popping up and flooding the town with demons and monsters. The only thing keeping Showside safe is Kit and his friends Belle and Moon. From the writer/artist of Adventure Time Candy Capers and Bravest Warrior comes an all ages romp with a horror twist.

The start of a brand-new arc!

As the Past Aways face a backlash from the US government, resident brawler Marge investigates an immortal teammate’s impossible murder. Meanwhile, a terrifying trio of ultra-evolvedsapiens emerges from the timestream to wreak havoc on modern soil!
Enter…the nefarious Dr. Gargunza! Devoid of any conscience, Marvelman finds a terrifying new foe in the doctor.
Marvelman enters a sci-fi nightmare when he goes up against a living computer!
Micky Moran gets a chilly reception from the Abominable Snowman!
You're not seeing double! That's another Marvelman on the cover! But just who is the doppelganger that bears an uncanny resemblance to Moran?
Marvelman enters the sleepy realm of Nod! But all is not as it seems in this fairytale kingdom…

name: Dennis ist der Beste - Ein Abenteuer kommt selten allein

description: Special Halloween issue, introducing a new major character!

When Polly Normandy earns a “special detention,” Carter and his friends get closer to learning the connection between Miss Crowe, Ms. Frump and the otherworldly creatures that have invaded Alabaster Shadows. But with Mr. Randolph out of commission, the kids have to take on the Community Council by themselves. Otherwise, their parents are toast.
name: Chapter Four

deck: Halloween in Gotham introduces two new rogues to The Dynamic Duo!
description: Two new additions to the ’66 Rogues Gallery are introduced in two stories. The Scarecrow is here to say “boo” to the good citizens of Gotham City, and to chase off the Caped Crusader. Then, a former henchman of King Tut has taken on a green, scaly look and roams the sewers under the city streets!
name: Scarecrow Comes To Town

description:
In School Spirit, the prom is here at last, but after everything that's happened, the gang may not get a happy ending...

In Ruined, Catherine and Andrew try to find a way to coexist peacefully - if a bit awkwardly - and Andrew makes an interesting proposition.

And in Beauties, Marguerite Bennett and Trungles introduce readers to a world of fantasy and desire that knows no bounds - and love between a beautiful young woman and her father's captive.

Plus, a sex column about safer sex, an essay about dating while genderqueer, a process peek at Beauties, and more!
name: School Spirit; Ruined; Beauties

description: Dr. George Herbert’s paradise has been compromised by Luthor’s henchmen, but Wonder Woman is determined to save the Cheetah—both body and soul! “Island of Lost Souls” part 3 of 3.
name: Island of Lost Souls Part 3 of 3

description: Musty the Mustang, beloved mascot of Midtown High, has been kidnapped! Spider-Man and the gang are busy with training and must decide if a rescue mission for Musty is a priority!
Dave and Femmie, who live on a small asteroid and run a junkyard business, detect a wrecked ship in outer space. When they investigate they find they are not alone.
name: Fuelish Endeavors

description:
The penultimate issue of Aliens Vs. Zombies is here! When a meteor carrying the Zombie virus hits Earth it triggers the potential end of mankind. The last chance for humanity is the spacecraft full of Alien scientists tasked with eliminating the interstellar virus.

Straight from the Free Comic Book Day release and based on the animated shorts seen on Angry Birds ToonsTV with over 30 Million views worldwide, 'CHAKRA THE INVINCIBLE' is the latest superhero from legendary creator, STAN LEE. In this issue, Raju continues to channel his new-found mystical chakra powers under Dr. Singh's guidance to save the city of Mumbai from supervillians!

Following issue 1's cliffhangers, Samwi and Professor Jang come under attack from the Yeti-like Yeren as Tovar journeys into the earth with an ancient necrophage cult. The dinosaur riding Nazi pygmies are all set to eat Amelia as Victor explores a seemingly deserted Nazi base. And we find out what the most haunted house has in store for Belasco and co.
